    <string name="monday_thursday_fasting_subtitle">The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: The deeds are presented on Monday and Thursday. Thus, I love for my deeds to be presented while I am fasting.</string>
    <string name="white_days_fasting_subtitle">The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to command the companions to fast the days of the white (nights): thirteenth, fourteenth and fifteenth of the month. He said: This is like keeping perpetual fast.</string>
    <string name="arfa_fasting_subtitle">The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: Fasting on the Day of Arafah, I hope from Allah, expiates for the sins of the year before and the year after.</string>
    <string name="tasua_fasting_subtitle">The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: When the next year comes, God willing, we would observe fast on the 9th.</string>
    <string name="ashora_fasting_subtitle">The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: Fasting the day of \'Ashura\', I hope, will expiate for the sins of the previous year.</string>
    <string name="shawwal_fasting_subtitle">The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: Whoever fasts during the month of Ramadan and then follows it with six days of Shawwal will be (rewarded) as if he had fasted the entire year.</string>
    <string name="ramadan_event_subtitle">The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: When the month of Ramadan starts, the gates of the heaven are opened and the gates of Hell are closed and the devils are chained.</string>
    <string name="ramadan_last_10_days_event_subtitle">Allah says: The Night of Decree is better than a thousand months. [97:3]</string>
    <string name="dhu_al_hijjah_first_10_days_event_subtitle">The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: There are no days during which righteous deeds are more beloved to Allah than these days.</string>
    <string name="eids_event_subtitle">Allah says: That is so. And whoever honours the symbols of Allah, it is certainly out of the piety of the heart. [22:32]</string>
    <string name="friday_event_subtitle">The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: If anyone recites sura al-Kahf (Quran, 18) on Friday, light will shine brightly for him till the next Friday.</string>
    <string name="sacred_months_event_subtitle">Allah says regarding the sacred months: so do not wrong yourselves during them. [9:36]</string>

